headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored a career-high 50 points, and the Orlando Magic beat the Indiana Pacers 119-115 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero stars as the Orlando Magic beat the Indiana Pacers 119-115

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma had 25 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists, and the Washington Wizards beat the Atlanta Hawks 121-119 on Monday night for their first win this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma scores 25 as the Wizards pick up their first win with a 121-119 victory over Hawks

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 30 points, Payton Pritchard came off the bench and hit eight 3-pointers en route to 28 points, and the Boston Celtics beat the Milwaukee Bucks 119-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaylen Brown scores 30 points, Payton Pritchard makes 8 3s as Celtics beat Bucks 119-108

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored a season-high 34 points, 15 in the fourth quarter, and the Cleveland Cavaliers improved to 4-0 by beating the New York Knicks 110-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 34 points to rally Cavaliers past the Knicks 110-104 for a 4-0 start

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored seven of his 40 points in overtime, and the Denver Nuggets overcame a 15-point deficit to beat the Toronto Raptors 127-125 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic scores 40, Nuggets rally from 15 down to beat Raptors for first win of season

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 30 points, including 11 in the fourth quarter to key a Chicago comeback as the Bulls defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 126-123 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, Vucevic key fourth-quarter rally as Bulls defeat Grizzlies 126-123

events.name: Houston Rockets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 34 points and the Houston Rockets never trailed in a 106-101 victory over Victor Wembanyama and the San Antonio Spurs on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 34 points and Rockets beat Spurs 106-101 to split 2-game set

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 23 points and Klay Thompson added 18 to lift the Dallas Mavericks over the Utah Jazz 110-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving scores 23 points to lead Mavericks past Jazz 110-102

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 33 points, Kevin Durant added 30 and the Phoenix Suns rallied to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 109-105 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 33, Durant adds 30 as the Suns rally for 109-105 win and hand Lakers first loss

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Sacramento Kings
